metadata.name: Slumbers #298
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: GENERATIVE GLASSES #86
metadata.description:
After 4 months of coding the Generative Glasses is ready! I gained a lot of experience along the way and I really liked the creation process.

I wrote an article in which I report on the creation process in more detail. It can be found at the bottom of the page for related articles.

üëì thousands of different outputs are possible
üë®‚Äçüíª only code
üé® 3D (#webGL #threejs) and 2D (#html5canvas) layers 
üé• animated
üñ±Ô∏è interactive (+controls for mobile)
üòé augmented reality view
üü• different previews: abstract view, product design view, and 2 other view
üñºÔ∏è save images from current view in 4k - 3 different aspect ratio
üìº save animation (from server side) on http://carco.hu

Compositions:

- There is an abstract view where the parts of the glasses are scattered
- There is a front-right view
- Front-left view
- Top view
- Product design view that converts to split screen
- Front view where the object falls apart and starts from the abstract view again

First, one of the 6 compositions comes in and the animation starts. The system randomly determines which composition should be the first in the line. This will also be the saved image that the fxhash system creates. 

If you don't click or touch anything, the animation will loop continuously. If you click into the area anywhere, the controller will appear and the animation will stop. Until you get to the next composition and the animation stops, the pause button flashes until now you can't press anything, all buttons are disabled. If the animation has stopped, the buttons are enabled again, and you can move the camera in 3D space by dragging. 

The controls have left and right arrows that can be used to step between compositions. The animation restarts with the play button.

There are also a few other buttons:

- There is a save button which is a floppy disk. A menu will then appear, offering to save images of different proportions, with the default aspect ratio generated by the program code at the top. (Opening in a new window is required to save an image)

- There is a camera icon that restores the original camera view. It is worth pressing this before saving.

There are options that are not available for all compositions, they only appear if they are enabled in current composition:

- Switch split screen to main camera view, and back (4 squares icon)
- Shows and hide Editing lines (pair of compasses)
- Shows and hide Callout notations (pencil and ruler)
- Shows AR view and stop it (cube icon) (Opening in a new window is required to AR view, more info below)

Keyboard controls:

Press ‚Äú5‚Äù to save image to default aspect ratio
Press ‚Äú6‚Äù to save image to square aspect ratio
Press ‚Äú7‚Äù to save image to portrait aspect ratio
Press ‚Äú8‚Äù to save image to landscape aspect ratio

(Opening in a new window is required to save an image)

Press ‚ÄúArrowDown‚Äù for restores the original camera view
Press ‚ÄúD‚Äù to switch to next composition
Press ‚ÄúA‚Äù to switch  to previous composition
Press ‚ÄúS‚Äù to start animation
Press ‚ÄúSpacebar‚Äù to switch to split screen (if it is available)
Press ‚Äú1‚Äù to hide/show Editing lines (if it is available)
Press ‚Äú2‚Äù to hide/show Callout notations (if it is available)
Press ‚Äú3‚Äù to hide/show AR view (Opening in a new window is required to AR view, more info below)

AR view

If you have a camera on your device, you can try out how such glasses would suit you. This function is not available for all compositions, so if you cannot find the cube icon, tab to the next composition and click on the cube icon. I created this function with the help of Tensorflow face landmark detection package. It's not perfect, there are delays, but it's good enough to try out the glasses.

More information on how were made Generative Glasses in the related article below.

Thank you for your attention! Thanks for the support! Thanks for the opportunity fxhash and genart community! I hope I was able to contribute to generative art with my work!

@C4RC0
carco.hu

metadata.name: Turpentine #4
metadata.description:
This token generates abstract digital paintings in the style of oil paintings. Brushstrokes are simulated by using noise and random functions. Each painting uses a two-color palette (in rare cases only single color might be used).

- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view.
- press '1' to save 2400x2400 PNG image
- press '2' to save 4000x4000 PNG image
- press '3' to save 5600x5600 PNG image
- press '4' to save 7200x7200 PNG image

The artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

NFT Licence
March 2022.

metadata.name: Pyramids Age #45
metadata.description: An abstraction of pyramids and circuit combination that target Slavery in the age of technology. so I named it Pyramids Age. the lines create you a pyramid and the inside as chaos. The complexity and beautiful order of electronic circuits causes distraction, and this beauty used in wrong ways.

metadata.name: codeTurning 2: push&POPing #42
metadata.description:
The codeTurning project aims to reflect my journey from traditional tools to code, in which any day I learn a new skill.
Join me towards something new for me. Something different from the previous.
Sometimes we will stand on the shoulders of giants.
 
Let's explore and see how far we get.
 
Lesson 2: push&POPing
 
With the sole initial aim of exploring push() and pop(), this stop along the way allows us to delve into the beautiful whimsy of basic colored geometric shapes. I'm having fun.

metadata.name: Livro #125
metadata.description:
A messy book is a well-read book, a sign of knowledge acquired. It's easy to spot a book that has been loved and used frequently. The pages are bent and creased, the spine is worn, and notes are scribbled in the margins. These imperfections are not a sign of neglect or carelessness, but rather an evidence of a book that has been fully engaged with and understood.
A book that is kept in pristine condition may look nice on a shelf, but it is also a sign that it has not been read as much, or not as deeply. A well-read book is an indication of a curious and active mind, always seeking to learn and grow. So, don't be afraid to let your books get a little messy, it's a sign that you're gaining knowledge and expanding your understanding of the world around you.

Made with p5.js, p5.grain and much love <3

[S] to save as image

metadata.name: Corroding Cubes #41
metadata.description:
The kaleidoscopic pillars, once soaring emblems of the city's soul, had now succumbed to the relentless onslaught of time. Yet, as they crumbled and decayed, their colors remained steadfast, a radiant symphony of hues that defied the erosion of age. The people looked up at the pillars, and in their decline, they saw a reflection of their own trials and victories.

metadata.name: Oddball #14
metadata.description:
Oddball is an expansion of the piece I created for day 7 of Genuary 2023. The prompt: Sample a color palette from your favorite movie/album cover. All seven palettes in this project were sampled from the album cover for Insolito by Tipper (https://tipper.bandcamp.com/album/insolito). 

The project title is a play on insolito meaning "unusual" and the featured bubble-like cellular noise. These bubbles are used to warp low-frequency simplex noise. When combined with the vibrant palettes, striking psychedelic patterns appear.

Controls:

[space] or click to toggle animation
[r] to reset animation to static view
[s] to save as 4000x4000 PNG
[t] to toggle paper texture

#genuary32nd

metadata.name: let me fall #403
metadata.description:
A study of form, empty spaces, panic attacks, asymmetry, tinnitus, chaos, and the never-ending journey to obtain imperfection. 

30 Matisse-inspired palettes.

2-6 ‚Äì increase resolution.

‚Äúf‚Äù ‚Äì add more noise to iteration at current resolution.
‚Äún‚Äù ‚Äì redraw at current resolution without noise.
‚Äús‚Äù ‚Äì save export.

Please be patient while drawing at higher resolutions, it can take quite a while.

Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Contraformas #72
metadata.description:
Shapes are drawn on a space-filling grid against other shapes, using a random walk algorithm. then they are separated with a random offset, hence the name counterforms (contraformas).

created by @mdollinger with p5js

metadata.name: Quantum Vacuum #533
metadata.description:
Empty space is not empty. It's filled with energy, transient fluctuations in quantum fields, bubbling with virtual particles popping in and out of existence. 

Part of an ongoing series of work combining my fascination with the fringes of fundamental physics, the emergence of complex behaviour through the interaction of very simple rules, and my obsession with hacking our perceptual systems. 

/Disclaimer: This is not a simulation, but an artistic conceptual interpretation and dramatization. :)

metadata.name: YYYSEED #928
metadata.description:
üî• BURN NOTICE: This is a FIVE DAY "open edition" to celebrate the launch of fx(params). The project is open for minting from the start of Monday until midnight Friday (GMT).

YYYSEED is an artwork with an aesthetic that works across digital, print and pen plotting mediums, leaning towards the minimalistic nature of drawing machines. SVGs can be exported for this purpose.

I've designed the algorithm to work best for this with the default settings, you should be good to go right out of the box. You can explore the design space a little further using the parameters (more details below).

If you're planning on plotting the work at larger sizes (A2, A1), then the "Override suggest lines" is there for you to cram more of them into the extra space.

PARAMS ::::::::::::::

The initial settings of the parameters are what I think best for the look I'm trying to achieve as the artist: minimal pen plotting work. This comes from the "Suggested" and "Random for hash" values.

You can take the design away from that by turning the "Use suggested lines" and "Use suggested destroyer" options off, and using your own values with the slider.

"Random for hash" means the feature has been randomly selected and fixed for the current hash and won't change. For example, if the hash is 'ooABCD' and the grid's "Random for hash" picks 3x4, then it will always be 3x4 for that hash, it isn't random each time you change sometime. Picking a new hash however will then randomly pick a new (fixed) option.

DANGER SEED :::::::::

USE OF THE DANGER SEED IS NOT RECOMMENDED. If you set the DANGER SEED, the value will be encoded along with the rest of the params (where it can be decoded) in the stored data of the mint, along with the token.

The DANGER SEED will only take effect if it starts with 'YYY', it will STOMP all over the other settings, including the hash.

INSTRUCTIONS ::::::::

h - Toggle highres mode on/off (starts off)
t - Toggle paper background on/off
s - Save png (in highres if toggled on)
1-6 - Save SVGs for plotting A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6

PEN PLOTTING ::::::::

Press 1-6 to select which A1-6 size paper you want to plot onto, the the system will download one or more files for you to use, one file per colour.

Please tag #plottertwitter, or #penplotter on twitter, instagram & mastodon

PRINTING ::::::::::::

The output of the high resolution version is 6,144 x 8,192 pixels. That will print at the following sizes.

300dpi: 20.48 x 27.31 inches (52.02 x 69.35 cm)
200dpi: 30.72 x 40.96 inches (78.03 x 104.03 cm)

300dpi is recommended, but 200dpi should be fine for this design. I suggest turning the paper texture off if you're printing onto textured archival paper, you can leave it on when printing onto smooth white paper.

metadata.name: Dentro #59
metadata.description:
"Dentro" 

Dentro is a captivating art form that captures the multifaceted beauty within each of us. It showcases a diverse range of flowers, from vibrant and vivid to dark and mysterious, mirroring the rich tapestry of our inner souls. These intricate patterns and colors reveal the unique complexities of our emotions, experiences, and perspectives, inviting viewers to explore and embrace the depth of human existence.

It is fully personalized, you can create your own palette to it (just need to check the option for a personalized palette)

made with p5.js, p5.grain and GLSL
Zamboni, March 2023

metadata.name: Bouquet num√©rique #222
metadata.description:
This generative automaton specializes in making pencil drawings of flower bouquets. It represents an attempt to capture some of the shapes, textures and nuances typical of hand-made drawings through algorithmic means. 

It is a continuation of the exploration initiated with my previous work ‚ÄúThe Likeness of a Flower‚Äù, a generator of expressionist flower paintings.

Strongly inspired by the astonishing work of British artist Claudia Lowry: https://www.instagram.com/claudialowry_art/

100% code ‚Äì no assets. Made with p5.js.
This work is animated.

Controls:
[SPACE] to play/pause
[r] to restart the drawing
[f] to toggle fullscreen
[s] to download capture
[2] to [9] to generate and save a hi-res image at multiples of the original 1000 x 1000 resolution. Please note that rendering at high resolutions can be slow.
